Fastest service in the west!  Stopped by here for a quick bite to eat. There was a line, but it moved quickly. Once I placed my order, the server already had my chicken sandwich in front of me before the manager could even swipe my card! Talk about fast! Coincidentally I recognized the manager from another restaurant he used to manage years ago.  Overall the place is clean, prices are wallet friendly & the service is quick. My only gripe is that the chicken sandwich wasn't as good as other Popeyes I've been to (breading was kind of soggy & mealy which is a problem I occasionally have with KFC breading.) Other than that everything is great!

We eat here all the time, but the franchisee just decided on this most recent visit that there are no free drink refills, and that refills are $1.00 - which is pretty obnoxious when a large drink costs $2.95. We eat here every week or so, and it's short-sighted decisions like this one that cause long time customers to choose other places. A good friend of mine termed this "Excel thinking" - where a spreadsheet causes a business to make decisions based on incomplete data; and the spreadsheet doesn't have a column that shows customers who no longer visit the business because of this sort of thing. As it is, I took away a star from my review because of this.  Update: They got rid of the no refill policy!

Made a Christmas order - it was messed up at nearly every step possible.  Then when I called to see how to rectify, they told me to come in tomorrow with receipt, of course, for full refund.  Got there next day, and the on duty manager said she was informed of the situation, and proceeded to reduce the refund because, in her words "The food went out".  I know she's doing her job, but by phone, the staff admitted to the "extra busy" circumstances, and likelihood of mistakes having been made.  I loved having a self started 20 year Christmas tradition.  That is now a painful memory, rather than the source of warm hope it once was.   Still in love with the chain, but this particular location, never again.
